The goal of this example is to test the density, density gradient, Laplacian of the density,
as well as the theoretical quantum pressure gradient. The quantities are computed for a Plummer
sphere using the SPH method and compared to the theoretical ground truth.

To generate the initial conditions locally, if pNbody is installed, run:

./makeICs.py


To run this example with the ULDM SPH solver, SWIFT must be configured with the following options:
 
./configure --with-hydro="uldm" --with-kernel=cubic-spline

To start the simulation:

./run.sh

To compare SPH quantities with analytical ones:

./plot.py snap/snapshot_0000.hdf5


